ENTRY            A1402   20260218   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A1402001   20260218   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  9         15
TITLE      Gamma radiation from proton bombardment of Li-7
AUTHOR     (A.A.Kraus Jr)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,93,1308,1954)
INSTITUTE  (1USACAL)
FACILITY   (VDG,1USACAL)
SAMPLE     Li-natural. The target thickness was about 30 keV.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) NaI(Tl) crystal 1.5 in. in diam. and 2 in.
           long, cemented to a 5819 photomultiplier tube.
METHOD     (PHD)
HISTORY    (19800730C) Compilation produced by Arzamas RFNC-VNIIEF
           (19990220U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20180421U) SD: BIB was updated in all Subents.
           (20260218A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           Subents 004, 005 deleted (relative tabulated values are
           given in ADD-RES in Subent 002).
ENDBIB              15
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           18
SUBENT        A1402002   20260218   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  5         17
REACTION   (3-LI-7(P,G)4-BE-8,PAR,DA,,REL)
           Gamma counts.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
ADD-RES     Cosine coefficients obtained by fitting a differential
           cross section in relative units are:
             energy         A0           A1             A2
             MeV     relative units relative units relative units
              0.880         112.            16.          32.
              0.960         130.            18.          36.
              1.060         134.            70.          44.
              1.140          98.            56.          40.
              1.240          88.            48.          48.
STATUS     (CURVE,,A.A.Kraus Jr,J,PR,93,1308,1954) Figs 2,3,4,5,6
HISTORY    (20180421A) SD: SF5=PAR added, SF9=EXP deleted from
           REACTION code. COS-ERR -> COS-ERR-D. E-MIN added.
           (20260218A) SD: STATUS updated. COS-CM -> COS;
           DATA-CM -> DATA.
ENDBIB              17
